We note that our primary dataset from 1970 to 1989 was during a period when ocean bottom temperature remained within the cod’s preferred range. Consequently, we could not explore the potential of long-term warming in particular to drive a deepening response in the stock as a whole. Even if a warming were observed our analysis indicates, given the survey design, that 13–14 y of data (
  
   SI Appendix, Table S5
  ) are required to achieve reliable estimates of biomass-related parameters such as the CM.
